h3 Connect to CSV Data

.row
  .col-sm-12
    label(for="url") Url
    input.form-control(type="text" data-tableau-key="url")
    p.help-block
      | Use this URL to load a sample CSV file:
      code https://www.quandl.com/api/v1/datasets/MADDISON/GDPPC_CHN.csv

.row

  .col-sm-4
    label(for="csv-quotes") Quotes
    select#csv-quotes.form-control(data-tableau-key="quote")
      option(value='"') " : Double quotes
      option(value="'") ' : Single quote
      option(value="`") ` : Backticks

    p.help-block
      | The character used to quote the fields. Defaults to <code>"</code>. Must
      | be a single character.

  .col-sm-4
    label(for="csv-delimieter") Delimiter
    select#csv-delimiter.form-control(data-tableau-source="csv" data-tableau-key="delimiter")
      option(value=",") , : Colon
      option(value=";") ; : Semicolon
      option(value="|") | : Pipe
      option(value="TAB") t : Tab

    p.help-block
      | The character used to separate the fields. Defaults to <code>,</code>.
      | Must be a single character.

  .col-sm-4
    label(for="csv-charset") Charset
    select#csv-charset.form-control(data-tableau-key="charset")

      optgroup(label="Web Standards")
        option(value="UTF-8") UTF-8
        option(value="ISO8859-1") ISO8859-1

      optgroup(label="Central European")
        option(value="ISO8859-2") ISO8859-2

    p.help-block
      | EXPERIMENTAL: depending on the server hosting the data, setting this may or may not fix
      | character encoding problems.


.row
  .col-sm-12
      a.btn.btn-default(href="#" data-state-to="run") Load CSV
